===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|broun|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|brun|brūn|lang=ang}} 'dark, shining', from {{proto|Germanic|brūnaz|lang=en}} (compare {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|brún|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|bruin|lang=nl}}, German {{term|braun|lang=de}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰruhₓnos}} (compare Ancient Greek {{term||phrýnē}}, {{term||phrŷnos}} ‘toad’), enlargement of {{proto|Indo-European|title=|bʰrew-|shiny, brown}} (compare {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|beras|bė́ras|lang=lt}} ‘brown’, Sanskrit {{term||babhrú}} ‘reddish-brown’ {{rfscript|Devanagari|lang=sa}}).

